list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Events now have a status associated to them

task.summary: Default task
Implemented scene with dimensions and position
Layers can now be added to a scene
Added fixed FPS game loop
Layers are now children of the scene Use of ref to reference the layers
Nodes can now be added to layers and are updated when layer gets updated
Nodes are now redrawn on the scene at fixed FPS
Scene now also accepts a single layer as child
Layer's context is now private
Rectangle is now abstract and does not implement the update method (no node should implement it)
Added support for nodes behaviours
Fixed undesired behaviours due to key down's code case sensitivity
Added support for grid drawing
Implemented grid movement (not correctly working if node has an offset on the layer)
Grid movement now working with custom cell sizes
Grid movement now working with offsets
Speed is now in pixels per frame
4-way movement doesn't allow diagonal movement anymore Implemented 8-way movement
Layers are now cleared correctly (taking into account the global translation of 0.5 pixels)
Added support for sprites drawing
Added support for sprite animation
Added missing resources
Minor refactoring
Slightly simplified behaviours
Improved event notification handling
Creating an instance of EventHandler for each event to handle isn't necessary anymore (replaced by a call to a static method)
Simplified events propagation and handling Introduced standardized events categories and types with enums
Fixed the fact that no event was fired during last bit of grid movement
Movements now use the universal "move" function
Universal "move" function is now the only movement function used
Events now have a status associated to them
